'''Annaram Barrage''' is an under construction irrigation project on Godavari River located at Annaram Village, [[Mahadevpur]] Mandal, [[Jayashankar Bhupalpally district]] in [[Telangana State]], [[India]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/telangana-cm-lays-foundation-for-kaleshwaram-irrigation-project/article8547044.ece|title=Telangana CM lays foundation for Kaleshwaram irrigation project|work=The Hindu BusinessLine|accessdate=4 September 2017 }}</ref>{{failed verification|date=November 2017}}
This is the second point and one of the barrages proposed in Kaleshwaram Project which envisages construction of three barrages between Yellampally & Medigadda.
'''Proposed Annaram Barrage details:''' {| class="wikitable" !Barrage !Bed level (m) !Pond Level (m) !Gross Storage (TMC) !Number of Gates |- |Annaram Barrage |107.0 |120.0 |11.9 |66 |}
==Project info== Annaram Barrage foundation was laid by First Chief Minister of Telangana, K.Chandrashekar Rao on 2 May 2016.{{Citation needed|date=December 2017}}
The project started by [[Telangana]] government as part of the Kaleshwaram Lift Irrigation Schema to irrigate the 18.5 lakh acres of new land and stabilize the 11.8 lakh acres of existing irrigated land.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Telangana/2016-05-02/Kaleshwaram-project-KCR-lays-foundation-stone/225617|title=Kaleshwaram project: KCR lays foundation stone|work=The Hans India|accessdate=4 September 2017 }}</ref>
